Here's the PlantUML sequence diagram for the Luizbrandt_users-crud-salesforce system:

```plantuml
@startuml Luizbrandt_users-crud-salesforce
title User CRUD Operations in Salesforce

actor Client
participant "API Kit Router" as Router
participant "CRUD Flow" as CRUDFlow
participant "DataWeave Transformer" as DW
participant "Salesforce Connector" as SF
database "Salesforce" as SFDB

Client -> Router: HTTP Request (CRUD operation)
Router -> CRUDFlow: Route based on operation type

alt Create/Update
    CRUDFlow -> DW: Transform request payload
    DW -> CRUDFlow: Transformed Salesforce object
    CRUDFlow -> SF: Execute operation
    SF -> SFDB: Create/Update record
    SFDB --> SF: Operation result
    SF --> CRUDFlow: Response
    CRUDFlow -> DW: Transform response
    DW --> CRUDFlow: Transformed response
else Read
    CRUDFlow -> SF: Query record(s)
    SF -> SFDB: Execute query
    SFDB --> SF: Query results
    SF --> CRUDFlow: Response
    CRUDFlow -> DW: Transform response
    DW --> CRUDFlow: Transformed response
else Delete
    CRUDFlow -> SF: Delete record
    SF -> SFDB: Execute deletion
    SFDB --> SF: Operation result
    SF --> CRUDFlow: Response
end

CRUDFlow --> Router: Operation response
Router --> Client: HTTP Response
@enduml
```